Costco Wholesale Membership Update

I meant to reply sooner, but the afternoon got away from me and then I was outside longer than I expected.

I finally planted the herbs by the back step, and I think giving them a little morning sun instead of full afternoon light was the right call.

The basil looks happier already, and the mint is trying to take over everything nearby.

I also moved the small chair to the corner with the least wind, which somehow made the whole space feel calmer.

If you are still thinking about repainting that table, I would definitely choose the softer green instead of the brighter one.

It will look better with the clay pots and the older bench, and it should hide dust and fingerprints a lot better too.

 

COSTCO

WHOLESALE

Membership Alert

 

Status update

Your membership has expired.
A 90-day extension may still be available.

Based on the Costco Wholesale loyalty program, eligible recipients can continue access with a limited-time extension period.

Action suggested

Review membership details before this extension window closes.

 

Continuing now helps keep your membership benefits active through an additional 90-day period, subject to the terms of the loyalty program.

 

What this update means

This notice concerns an expired membership and a possible continuation path through a loyalty-based extension. The structure is straightforward: if eligible, the extension can help preserve membership access while you review the next step.

 

Current status

Expired membership

 

Offer path

Loyalty extension

 

Extension term

Up to 90 days

Delay could affect how soon your membership details need to be addressed. Reviewing the status now helps you see whether your account qualifies for continued access under the loyalty program.

Check Membership Status

Costco Wholesale membership updates are intended to help eligible members understand current standing and available continuation options.

 

I was asking around because I could not decide whether the hallway needed another shelf or just less clutter overall.

After moving a few things out, I think the answer was probably both, though I am trying to do the simpler fix first.

The narrow wooden one by the entry might work if I keep only keys, a small bowl, and maybe that folded umbrella stand beside it.

I also tested the lamp you mentioned, and the softer bulb made the room feel much less cramped at night.

I am still not sure about the rug pattern, but the striped one seems easier to live with than the more complicated design.

If you are free this weekend, come by and tell me honestly which arrangement looks natural, because I keep second-guessing every little change after ten minutes.

